==English==

===Etymology===
[[Onomatopoeic]]

===Pronunciation===
*pēp, /piːp/, /<tt>pi:p</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːp|Rhymes: -iːp]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|peeps|peeping|peeped}}

# To [[look]], while trying not to be [[see]]n or [[notice]]d.
#:''The man '''peeped''' through the small hole.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A quiet sound, particularly one from a baby bird.
# A feeble utterance or complaint.
#:''I don't want to hear a '''peep''' out of you''!

